Source:  Sheep Farming in NZ
Author:  PERRY
Vol / Page:  16
Edition:
Quote:  The shearing board should be of a good width, and be separated from the holding pens by a solid wall, so as to facilitate penning up. The floor of the pens should be of battens, with sufficient space between to allow droppings to fall through.
